<br>
Suggesting a rotation on a mob that is neither hunted exclusively for his tangible items nor is, more importantly, contested on anything close to a regular basis is, I say, going against the spirit of the RTA.  Will he ever be pharmed primarily for the items he drops (to the point that he is contested), rather than the access to the zone he provides?  You know what, I don't know ...I'm not a psychic ...but right now, today, he is not killed for his tangible items, he is killed for the flag ...a flag that can be quested for individually over a much longer period of time ...a flag that for all intents and purposes only needs to be done very very few times by each guild ...and any attempt to control by rotation the killing of that mob (awarding of that flag) can only be seen as a means to slow the progression of anyone wishing access to the zone in question.  If ...and I say IF because the sheer possibility is in question ...IF AD is ever <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>contested</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> primarily for his tangible loot table, THEN and only then should he be a candidate for rotation.  That is simply not the case right now.<br>
<br>
The problem we have here is not that people are saying 'teh rotations is teh suck on AD&quot;, excluding your personal whipping boy Dytren.  I think most of us agree with the rotation system in principle, but the only legitimate reason for suggesting AD be added to a rotation right now is the fact that a couple of guilds teamed up on him, beat him, and OMG he has to go on rotation now so that we can enforce the 'no teaming on rotation mobs' rule.  That's it.  Let's extrapolate a minute:  'teh rotations is teh suck on AD when it is only being placed on rotation to keep us newbs outta the ubah zones'.  I'm getting pretty good at this extrapolation crap.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So, the issue is that<br>
a) because the mob drops a key, and<br>
