<br>
can·di·date    ( P )  Pronunciation Key  (knd-dt, -dt)<br>
n. <br>
1. A person who seeks or is nominated for an office, prize, or honor. <br>
2. A student who has nearly completed the requirements for a degree. <br>
3. One that seems likely to gain a certain position or come to a certain fate: young actors who are candidates for stardom; a memorandum that is a good candidate for the trash can. <br>
