 <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=159651" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Eriadocc Elessidill -- Gnome Powah Wizzy -- Far Seekers, The Rathe</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gatorivonhinx>Gatori Vonhinx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/10/03 10:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=178>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.  </span><hr size=1> In defense of BotS, they have no need to cockblock HoH, they are barely affected by new people in the zone.  In the two weeks of access to HoH that CB has had, I have seen someone from that guild in the zone once . . . and there were 45 of them total.  HoH isn't a BotS playground.<br>
<br>
The question here isn't how rotations are set up, who decides rotation rules or the value of rotations to the smaller guilds.  All of this is obvious.  <br>
<br>
Rotations are nothing more than formalized agreements between the people killing a given mob (not necessarily those that CAN kill it) that there is greater demand for than avaiability.  A rotation rule, thus, can be changed if agreed upon by all members of that rotation.  For example, if all 4 or 5 members (too lazy to look atm) of the Dozekar rotation wanted to make the rule regarding names that they can be killed by the guild up for Dozekar from the day he spawns until the day the next spawns, we could do so . . . provided we all agree.  This is the reason that United Necros has no say in the RZ rotation.  <br>
<br>
The true question here is whether rotation rules can be applied to mobs that are not on rotation.  I would tend to favor the opinion that they shouldn't apply, but I see the point about the potential for teaming all of the way up to RZ (but not beyond).  PoP has altered the current framework in use on the Rathe and instead of trying to stretch the rules in existance regarding these mobs, we should either: <br>
<br>
a) Put them on rotation.  If guilds teaming up on every mob before RZ (not saying that CB/VoLS would do that) is viewed as a problem that is greater than the effort of killing them by the guilds currently capable of doing so, put them on rot.  I can guarantee that will end the teaming right there.<br>
<br>
b) Make up a new rule-set for flag-giving mobs.  This is the one where you will be standing on the weakest legal ground.  There is no reason to do this.  Especially if the mobs remain uncontested.  A better comparison than the ones that I keep seeing is Sontalak or LTK.  Nobody on the server would care if VoLS and CB teamed to get more ST keys by killing these guys, especially Sont (who is a remarkable pain in the ass and drops nothing of value save the talisman).  <br>
<br>
c) Admit that these mobs are FCFS in light of their uncontested nature and allow teaming as is the case with VS, Gore, Tal, Fay, Woushi, the little one in CS, all WW dragons save 1 and WToV. <p>Gatori Vonhinx<br>
