<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The entire idea of joining a rotation is that you are breaking into that rotation. Now in most circumstances, many guilds are willing to give a guild who asks a shot at the mob, but in some cases they may not. This is where racing to that mob may be necessary. You don't have the right to call for a rule change to a rotational mob just because it might make it easier for you to join that rotation.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Really?  Wow.  Absolutely wonderful expose'.  What rotation mob are we attempting to make a rule change on again?  I forgot.<br>
