<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Many people seem to cry foul of the bigger guilds who are supposedly stifling their chance to grow and access new content. It is not logical to argue that BotS was able to do so well because they got to kill content with no competition for so long, and thus because of rotations, smaller guilds can no longer able to grow as fast because of this. Surely everyone can see that the prize of working hard and getting there first is to have little or no competition on content. It has always been the case in EQ that if you are ahead of the curve you will have more opportunities than those below you.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You were on crack when you wrote this, weren't you?  Cmon, admit it.  I cannot determine what left field this came out of ...I'd be happy with narrowing down the state the ballpark is in.<br>
