<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This thread has nothing to do with people saying that what CB and VoLS did was against the rules. It wasn't, and that is exactly what this thread is about. Most of those who have killed Aerin`Dar by themselves are not happy with the situation of guilds teaming up on non rotation mobs then killing their rotation mobs as seperate entities. The idea here is to try and establish a set of rules that is fair for everyone and doesn't create any double standards as currently exist.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Hello, Oxy, meet Moron.  You can't be 'right' and 'wrong' at the same time.  You are either 'right' and people are happy for you ...congrats, champagne all around! ...or you are 'wrong' and people 'scowl at you ready to attack'.  Which is it here?  Straddling the fence like that can have dire consequences for your ability to have opinions later.<br>
